{
  "texts": [
    "• The authors should reflect on the factors that influence the performance of the approach.For example, a facial recognition algorithm may perform poorly when image resolution is low or images are taken in low lighting.",
    "Or a speech-to-text system might not be used reliably to provide closed captions for online lectures because it fails to handle technical jargon.",
    "• The authors should discuss the computational efficiency of the proposed algorithms and how they scale with dataset size.",
    "• If applicable, the authors should discuss possible limitations of their approach to address problems of privacy and fairness.",
    "• While the authors might fear that complete honesty about limitations might be used by reviewers as grounds for rejection, a worse outcome might be that reviewers discover limitations that aren't acknowledged in the paper."
  ]
}